# Buzat, Sterlibashevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Buzat (; , Bu≈∫at) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Buzatovsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 722 as of 2010. There are 9 streets.
Geography
Buzat is located 46&nbsp;km southwest of Sterlibashevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Maly Buzat is the nearest rural locality.
